# Database Schema

Provider: **Supabase (PostgreSQL)**

## Tables

### `users`
- id (uuid, PK)
- email (text, unique)
- created_at (timestamptz)
- preferences (jsonb) — alert settings, watchlist

### `stocks`
- id (uuid, PK)
- ticker (text, unique) — e.g. "TSLA"
- name (text) — e.g. "Tesla Inc."
- sector (text)
- market_cap (numeric)
- last_price (numeric)
- updated_at (timestamptz)

### `sources`
- id (uuid, PK)
- name (text)
- url (text)
- credibility_score (float) — 0.0 to 1.0
- type (text) — "news", "press_release", "sec_filing"

### `news_articles`
- id (uuid, PK)
- source_id (uuid, FK → sources)
- headline (text)
- body (text)
- url (text, unique)
- published_at (timestamptz)
- fetched_at (timestamptz)
- tickers (text[]) — extracted ticker symbols
- sentiment_score (float) — -1.0 to 1.0
- event_type (text) — earnings, regulation, m&a, product, executive
- novelty_score (float)
- credibility_score (float)

### `events`
- id (uuid, PK)
- stock_id (uuid, FK → stocks)
- article_id (uuid, FK → news_articles)
- event_type (text)
- severity (float) — 0.0 to 1.0
- detected_at (timestamptz)

### `signals`
- id (uuid, PK)
- stock_id (uuid, FK → stocks)
- direction (text) — "bullish", "bearish", "crash_risk"
- confidence (float) — 0.0 to 1.0
- expected_move_low (float) — e.g. 0.03 (+3%)
- expected_move_high (float) — e.g. 0.07 (+7%)
- horizon_days (int) — 1, 5, 30, 90, 180
- opportunity_score (float)
- crash_risk_score (float)
- rank (int)
- explanation (text) — LLM-generated
- drivers (jsonb) — top factors
- evidence (jsonb) — article references
- historical_analog (jsonb) — avg move, hit rate
- risk_flags (text[])
- created_at (timestamptz)
- expires_at (timestamptz)

### `signal_history`
- id (uuid, PK)
- signal_id (uuid, FK → signals)
- stock_id (uuid, FK → stocks)
- direction (text)
- confidence (float)
- expected_move_low (float)
- expected_move_high (float)
- horizon_days (int)
- created_at (timestamptz)
- actual_move (float) — filled in after horizon passes
- was_correct (bool) — filled in after horizon passes
- accuracy_notes (text)

## Indexes
- `news_articles(published_at DESC)`
- `signals(stock_id, created_at DESC)`
- `signals(rank ASC)`
- `signal_history(stock_id, created_at DESC)`
